cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper deals with semi-supervised learning using deep Convolutional Neural Networks (ConvNets), which is a popular topic in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also proposes a regularization term that guides the decision boundary to lie on the low density space between the manifolds corresponding to different classes of data, which is related to the concept of neural manifold learning, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely category as well. Finally, the paper deals with object recognition, which is a common task in natural language processing, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible category.
